<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-264-412  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 264 412.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  May 15 1989 v23 n20 p33(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Voice challenges icon as computer interface. (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brandel, William.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Advanced Products and Technologies plans to market its Explorerhand-held computer in this country as soon as it is okayed by theFederal Communications Commission.andP;  The machine's input-outputcommands are voice activated.andP;  The systems will be introduced inEurope and Japan in June, 1989.andP;  Initially, the system will runonly English- and Spanish-language translation applications with aplug-in cartridge.andP;  The firm hopes to have traditionalapplications such as accounting and database on the market in thenear future.andP;  The Explorer measures 8.25 by 7 by 2.75 inches,weighs three pounds and is priced at $2,300.andP;  The machine isexpected to be on retailers' shelves by Jul 1989.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Advanced Products and Technologies Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    APTIC.andO;Product:   Advanced Products and Technologies Explorer (portable computer)(product introduction).andO;Topic:     Voice I-O EquipmentHand-held computersProduct Introduction.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>